						               													<description>So you enjoyed playing Battleship when you were young but grew out of it. Looking for an intense and MULTIPLAYER Naval Warfare board game, time to try... RHYOLITE BAY - Naval Warfare.&amp;#10;Up to 5 players can send their Naval Fleet into Rhyolite Bay for battle. Placement of your Ships is secret, only you know the locations. Take turns playing specialty cards to sink the opponent's naval fleet.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;ENHANCED ATTACK CARDS&amp;#10;Launch Bombs to sink enemy ships - single, double &amp;amp; triple hits.&amp;#10;Launch a Nuke Bomb to blow a whole area out of the water.&amp;#10;Set Time Bombs on enemy ships.&amp;#10;Sonar Ping the location of your enemy.&amp;#10;Gain Bonus Points every time you sink an enemy ship.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;DEFENSE &amp;amp; STRATEGY CARDS&amp;#10;Use Self Destruct to sink your own ship - before they do?&amp;#10;Use Misfired Bomb to stop their missile attack.&amp;#10;Deceive your enemy with hidden Naval Mines - false hits?&amp;#10;Use your Bandit Card to steal playing cards from other player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;WINNING THE GAME&amp;#10;When only one player remains with ships not sunk, the game ends and the player with the most bonus points from sinking other ships wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A Card and Board style game that will have you calling HIT and MISS. Battleship could only dream to be this good on the big board!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
